      "writtenOn": "2017-02-13T14:39:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm this still doesn\u0027t make sense that this definition works for tweak alpha then. Say I had an FP that does the following \"If input alpha \u003c\u003d 0.5 set RGB to 0.0, otherwise set RGB to 1.0, alpha stays inputAlpha. Then multiple that color by inputAlpha.\" With an input color of (1,1,1,1) and coverage of 0.5 I think this fails. Without tweak we would get (0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5), with tweak alpha we get (0,0,0,0.25). It seems like if with srcAlpha * F, if the F depends on srcAlpha in a \"non modulate\" way then this optimization can\u0027t be used.",
      "parentUuid": "636ff49e_8994dd04",
